        heading: "Why B2B Sales Reps Need Mobile Ordering Apps",
        headingId: "why-mobile-apps",
        content: "<p>B2B sales reps spend 60-70% of their time in the field — at customer sites, warehouses, trade shows, and on the road. If they can't capture orders, check inventory, and access customer pricing from their phone or tablet, they're leaving money on the table at every stop.</p><p>A <a href=\"/blog/best-b2b-ordering-apps-distributors\">B2B mobile ordering app</a> gives field reps:</p><ul><li><strong>Instant order capture:</strong> Enter orders on-site, eliminate paper forms and post-visit data entry</li><li><strong>Real-time pricing:</strong> See each customer's <a href=\"/blog/complete-guide-b2b-customer-specific-pricing\">negotiated prices</a>, volume discounts, and active promotions</li><li><strong>Live inventory:</strong> Check stock levels across all warehouses before promising delivery dates</li><li><strong>Order history:</strong> Review what the customer ordered last time for quick reorders</li><li><strong>Product catalog:</strong> Browse and search the full catalog with images, specs, and availability</li><li><strong>Offline capability:</strong> Take orders even in basements, rural areas, or walk-in coolers with <a href=\"/blog/why-an-offline-order-taking-app-is-essential-for-fmcg-and-industrial-b2b-sales\">no internet connectivity</a></li></ul>"
